    "Such an extension generalizes the model to encompass transformations involving division, merger, or realignment -core features of any political evolution.Fact A.1.2 For any delegation function δ ≡ δ i 0 j 0 ∶ I → I, and any p-structure (I, E) one has δE -i 0 = E -i 0.What characterizes an simplicial delegation is asserted in the following: Notations A.1.6 For any p-structure (I, E), any i 0, j 0 ∈ I, i 0 ≠ j 0: we put: E i 0 j 0 ∶= {s ∈ E| i 0 ∈ s ⇒ j 0 ∈ s} Proposition A.1.7 For any delegation function δ ≡ δ i 0 j 0 ∶ I → I, and any p-structure (I, E), the following statements are equivalent:(i)The delegation δ i 0 j 0 in (I, E) is friendly, (ii) E = E i 0 ↓ j 0 (iii) E max ⊂ E i 0 j 0 Proof.",
    "(i) ⇒ (ii).",
    "Let s ∈ E. If i 0 ∉ s then s ∈ E i 0 j 0.",
    "If i 0 ∈ s, then by assumption j 0 ∪ s ∈ E and therefore j 0 ∪ s ∈ E i 0 j 0.",
    "It follows that s ∈ E i 0 ↓ j 0."
